	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>What Services Are Covered Under the CDCP?</h2>
		<p>The CDCP covers a broad spectrum of essential oral health services aimed at preventing and treating dental issues. While specific coverage can vary based on individual eligibility, covered services generally include:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Preventive Services:</strong> Comprehensive dental exams, scaling (cleaning), polishing, and digital X-rays to catch problems early.</li>
			<li><strong>Restorative Services:</strong> Amalgam and composite (white) fillings to treat cavities and restore tooth function.</li>
			<li><strong>Oral Surgery:</strong> Tooth extractions, including problematic wisdom teeth.</li>
			<li><strong>Endodontic Services:</strong> Root canal treatments to save severely infected teeth.</li>
			<li><strong>Prosthodontic Services:</strong> Complete and partial removable dentures (pre-authorization may be required).</li>
		</ul>
		<p>For the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding eligibility criteria and application processes, please refer to the official <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/services/benefits/dental/dental-care-plan.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Government of Canada CDCP Website</a>.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Your CDCP Visit: What to Expect</h2>
		<p>We strive to make using your CDCP benefits as seamless as possible. When you book an appointment with us, simply mention that you are a CDCP patient. On the day of your visit, please bring your Sun Life CDCP member card and a valid piece of government-issued ID. Our administrative team will submit the claims directly to Sun Life on your behalf, so you only need to worry about your oral health.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions About CDCP</h2>
		<div class="faq">
			<details>
				<summary>Will I have to pay anything out of pocket?</summary>
				<p>It depends on your adjusted family net income. The CDCP may cover 70%, 80%, or 100% of the eligible costs based on established fee guides. If your coverage is less than 100%, you will be responsible for the remaining co-payment portion. We always provide a clear estimate before starting any treatment.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Does the CDCP cover cosmetic dentistry like teeth whitening?</summary>
				<p>No. The CDCP is designed for essential oral health care. Purely cosmetic procedures, such as teeth whitening or veneers, are not covered under the plan.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>I just received my CDCP card. How soon can I book an appointment?</summary>
				<p>You can book an appointment immediately, provided that your coverage start date (indicated in your welcome package from Sun Life) has already passed. Contact us today to schedule your visit.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Can you explain my CDCP benefits to me in Mandarin?</summary>
				<p>Yes, absolutely. Our <a href="/mandarin-speaking-dentist">Mandarin-speaking team</a> is fully trained on the CDCP framework and can explain your coverage, co-payments, and treatment plans clearly in Chinese.</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</section>

